<B>Four more scams to add this time.  Inconsistencies or misspellings are italicized.</B><P><B>Example 1:</B><P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2"><BR>Hail, Norrathian,<BR> <BR>    This is J. Smedley, President of Verant Interactive, and I want to<BR>tell you that you got a job in VI! <I>Congratulation!</I>  But to apply for job, you must give me your full name, address, Station login and<BR><I>password</I>, Thanks for your time!<BR> <BR>        J. Smedley<BR>        President of VI                            &gt;&gt;<BR> <BR>***from [EDITED]@Hotmail.com &lt;mailto:[EDITED]@Hotmail.com&gt; ***<BR></font><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Note:  John Smedley is indeed President/CEO of SOE/Verant.  However, he did not send this email out, nor do we use hotmail or yahoo email accounts.<P><B>Example 2:</B><BR> <BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2"><BR>&lt;&lt;  (Character name)     <BR>        You are in trouble now, you will be banned if you dont cooperate on this subject!  I dont want to ban you, but you need to tell me your login and password so i can clean up your bad account!   Thanks for your time<BR> <BR> <BR><I>Johnson Smith</I>,<BR><I>Sale</I> Rep.                                &gt;&gt;<BR> <BR>***From [EDITED]@yahoo.com &lt;mailto:[EDITED]@yahoo.com&gt; ***<BR></font><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR> <BR>Note:  This is an extremely bad attempt by someone to get player's passwords.  Please always remember SOE/Verant will <B>Never</B> ask for your password by email.  Also, we do not have an employee by the name of Johnson Smith. A thanks goes out to Spiritsinger from the Vazaelle server for letting us know about these poor scam attempts.<BR> <BR><B>Example 3:</B><P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2"><BR>This is a very easy thing to do. And very rewarding too. Ok, here's how<BR>you do it! Verant has set a robot up on most E-mail services you can<BR>think of, Yahoo, Hotmail, Excite, MyMail, EverQuest, etc. etc. And we<BR>discovered the easiest way to do it was through Hotmail (Well, if you<BR>are using Hotmail to send this that is) because Hotmail has its little<BR>Instant Send thing. Anyways, to the point. You have to E-mail this<BR>e-mail <I>addres:</I> <BR>[EDITED]@hotmail.com<BR>The Subject must be: Password Recovery<BR>And this is <I>hjow</I> you do it. Type in this EXACTLY how it is!<BR>On the first line put: &lt;!= =YOUR ACCOUNT NAME= =!&gt;<BR>On the 3rd line put: &lt;!= =YOUR ACCOUNT <I>PASSWORD</I>= =!&gt;<BR>and on the 7th line, put: &lt;!= =ACCOUNT NAME FROM WHICH YOU WANT <I>TE</I> PASSWORD= =!&gt;<BR>So it would look like this:<BR>&lt;!= =account name= =!&gt;<BR>&lt;!= =account <I>password</I>= =!&gt;<BR>&lt;!= =account name that you want password from= =!&gt;<BR> <BR>And there ya have it! It's that easy! We have gotten plenty of <I>password</I> that we like. Many accounts with some nice high <I>lvled</I> people and <I>ppl</I> with nice equipment. I hope you enjoy this as much as we had!!<BR></font><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR> <BR><B>Example 4:</B><P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2"><BR>OK, i have the best way to hack accounts on EverQuest!! ok heres what<BR>you do: e-mail [EDITED]@yahoo.com and type this in your <I>messag</I> or comment blank...type it exactly or it wont work include exclamation points periods and everything: (!your account name!)===(!your password!) , ok thats it! this will <I>completely</I> confuse verant and you end up <I>receiving</I> someone elses account and password back!  <BR>i have gotten 23 accounts like this with VERY high <I>lvl</I> chars on them and lots of quest gear! TRUST ME THIS WORKS!!! BUT DO IT FAST BEFORE VERANT FIXES THE PROBLEM!!!!<BR></font><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Note:  Thanks goes out to Gym Hall on letting us know about these last two examples of poor attempts at scams.  They appear to be done by the same person, but using different email addresses.<BR> <BR> <BR>Auric Flamewalker<BR>

